r sites that have been flagged as low quality or spam.</li><li>You must not abuse, harass, threaten, malign, flame or intimidate other StoryTellers, staff, others who use the Service, bloggers or others online. Nor may you upload, post or otherwise include any Content that is defamatory, libelous, tortuous, vulgar, obscene, invasive of privacy, racially or ethnically objectionable, hateful, promotes or provides instructional information about illegal activities, or promotes any act of cruelty to animals or certain vegetables.</li><li>You must not impersonate another StoryTellers or any official of Golbin. If you trick someone into thinking you're something you're not, we'll lock your account.</li><li>Thou shalt not create X-rated stories. Creating X-rated stories may result in having your story or entire account locked and/or deleted.</li><li>Your author bio pics MUST be G-rated. Using R or X-rated avatars may result in having your entire account deleted.</li><li>If Golbin Staff believes your story to be grossly miscategorized, they reserve the right to re-categorize your story right away or lock it.</li><li>You cannot create Stories or use the Service for any illegal or unauthorized purpose, or to promote or make solicitations for any illegal or unauthorized activity.</li><li>You cannot use the Service to distribute, share or solicit Content belonging to third parties without proper authorization from the owner(s) of that Content. You must respect the proprietary and intellectual property rights of others (including trademark, copyright and trade secrecy) in creating your Story. Golbin is a fair harbor platform and can't endorse the content on our pages; if you have an issue with another user's content, please contact that individual directly first. Failing that, please send us a note, and we may be able to review or lock the story in question.</li><li>You must not, in the use of Golbin, violate any Federal, state or local laws. You must comply with all local laws regarding online conduct and acceptable content.</li><li>The Golbin <b>Respect Everyone </b>Policy: You cannot abuse other authors, bloggers, organizations and individuals online and off. Wait, did we mention this one yet? Probably because we're serious. Abuse = flaming people in the Golbin forum, harming their stories for your own gain, publicly maligning other members of the community, emailing threatening notes to authors, and more. If our forum moderators or community report you for these activities, your stories could get locked or deleted.</li><li>You cannot transmit content in breach of a confidentiality or fiduciary obligation you may have.</li><li>We've said this already but it's worth saying again: You cannot attempt to automatically redirect surfers to other domains, mislead surfers of the origins of the Content contained in your Story, or use your Story as storage for remote loading or to a website outside of the Golbin website.</li><li>You may not develop restricted or password-only Stories, or hidden pages or images (those not linked to from another accessible page).</li><li>You cannot interfere with or disrupt the Service, or any servers or networks connected to the Service, or disobey any requirements, procedures, policies or regulations of networks connected to the Service.</li><li>You cannot collect or store personal data about other users, except that you may encourage surfers to contact you and you may, in return, contact them back.</li><li>You cannot promote &quot;get rich quick&quot; schemes, ebooks, videos or manuals on Golbin.</li><li>Golbin reserves the right to change our StoryRank algorithm at any time.</li><li><b>The end of spambait: </b>Some topics are just irresistible to spammers. These are topics that don't generally exist in the real world, that aren't particularly useful, and that are very profitable to people who spam. So, here's where we draw the line between junk and spam. There are topics we're just not going to let people write