 written by a person, for a person.</li><li>If you make lots and lots of cookie cutter stories, each one mirroring the next, we will probably delete them. See #1.</li><li>Hosting content used without permission, copied and pasted stories, and/or uncredited images and language is against our TOS. For best results, just be you.</li></ol></p></div><div class='section'><h3>4. The content: who owns it?</h3><p>As a StoryTellers, you will be able to incorporate various forms of Content into your Stories. Golbin does not claim ownership of the Content you place on your Story. The Content will be owned by you or a third party from whom you got permission to post the content. By placing Content on your Story, however, you grant Golbin a worldwide, royalty-free, and non-exclusive license, for as long as your Story is displayed on Golbin, to reproduce, display, modify, adapt and publish the Content solely for the purpose of displaying, distributing and promoting your Story on Golbin. Golbin may preserve and store Content, and may also disclose Content if required to do so by law or if Golbin believes in good faith that such preservation or disclosure is reasonably necessary to: <ul><li>comply with legal process (e.g., subpoenas); </li><li>enforce these Terms of Service; </li><li>respond to claims that any Content violates the rights of third parties; or </li><li>protect the rights, property, or personal safety of Golbin, its users and the public.</li></ul></p><p>The StoryTellers, and not Golbin, will be fully responsible for all Content that is uploaded, posted, transmitted or otherwise made available by the StoryTellers on his or her Story. Golbin cannot guarantee the accuracy, integrity or quality of such Content. Golbin does not pre-screen Content, but will have the right (but not the obligation) in its sole discretion to refuse or remove any Content in a Story for any reason, including Content that may violate these Terms, or that is otherwise objectionable. Golbin also cannot take responsibility for anything that your surfers may do in reliance on the Content you post in your Story. Bottom line: put it on your Story, you're responsible.</p><p></div><div class='section'><h3>5. About payments</h3>Golbin works on a 70-30 revenue sharing basis; that is you, as the author, get 70% of the income generated by your stories, and Golbin will keep 30% to recover costs. By registering for Golbin as a author, you are appointing Golbin as your agent to handle all Service transactions.</p><p>It's entirely possible that things will occur that will make it, in Golbin's sole discretion, impossible to maintain the structure described in this document. Hey, we're a startup, and we've taken zero venture capital. We may, for example, have to change the percentages or details of the Service. We agree that we will not make any financial changes retroactively. Any changes will be for future payments. If we do need to change any significant terms, we will notify you by email before any change occurs. At that point, you will have the option of removing your Story from the Service if you choose to stop working with the Service under the new structure.</p><p>The Service earns its income via display ads that we feature on your stories. Please note that per our partnership with Google AdSense, if they ask us to remove ads or lock a story that is promoting illegal activity or featuring content that violates our agreement with them, we will act to lock your story from view and will always let you know when we do. Furthermore, Google AdSense determines the type of ads that show up on stories, based on the content and tags you have put on the page. They may also turn on &quot;interest-based advertising&quot; as part of the AdSense program, which is a system that attempts to increase relevance of ads for your readers, based on other ads they've clicked in the AdSense network. As per Google: &quot;Interest-based advertising will allow advertisers to show ads based on a user's previous interactions with them, such as visits to advertiser website and also to reach users based on their interests (e.g. &quot;sports enthusiast&quot;). To develop interest categories, we will recognize the types of web pages users visit throughout the Google content network. As an example, if they visit a number of sports pages, we will add them to the &quot;sports enthusiast&quot; interest category.&quot;</p><p>Currently we support payment via NEFT only in India, and via PayPal elsewhere. If you are outside India, and if you cannot receive money via PayPal, then we cannot pay you. Sorry.</p><p><b>Forfeiture of Earnings: </b>There are several ways in which you may lose your reported Earnings. These include, without limitation, the following: </p><ul><li>If you in any way violate or otherwise breach these Terms of Service;</li><li>If you engage in any activity intended to, or the result of which could or would, defraud Golbin or any third party, including, without limitation, with respect to any advertising activity arising on your Story, taking any action (or authorizing any third party to take any action) to inflate or otherwise manipulate traffic or click-through counts from your Story to participating advertisers or merchants, or otherwise attempting, in Golbin's good faith judgment, to simulate artificially the behavior or activity of an individual live Web user.</li><li>If you list items for sale via an affiliate partner (like eBay or Amazon) just to buy from them yourself and otherwise inflate your commissions;</li><li>It's important to note that if you go more than twelve months without reaching a payout, we'll assume you've abandoned your account and that money will be returned to our system and applied to our overhead and our charity fund.</li></ul><p>In the event of any downtime of the site, or any technical problem the site may (heaven forfend!) undergo, Golbin, as a free service, is not responsible for compensating authors for perceived loss of earning potential. We historically go out of our way to make it up to authors, in your favor, when there is a demonstrable and specific and individual earning glitch. But by default we cannot treat earning potential the same as actual recorded earnings.</p><p>By using the Services, you acknowledge and agree that Golbin will not be responsible for, and will not be obligated in any manner to repay you for, any lost earnings.</p></div><div class='section'><h3>6. Resale of service</h3><p>You agree not to reproduce, duplicate, copy, or exploit any portion of the Service, use of the Service, or access to the Service, other than through the display and use of your story. This means you agree not to hijack content from other stories, plagiarize, set up false accounts, spam or hack stories, duplicate stories on other services, or exploit other users by selling them false information or services about Golbin.</p><p><strong>Prohibited uses: </strong>Golbin is designed to permit users to share information that is important to them. It's built around individuals and their passions. You're not permitted to spam Golbin to create stories for hire in order to generate web traffic and SEO rankings. It is fine to use Golbin to create stories about your business or even for your clients, but you may not cross the line and start creating pages in bulk.</p><p></div><div class='section'><h3>7. Golbin can modify or discontinue the service</h3>Golbin reserves the right at any time to modify or discontinue, temporarily or permanently, the Service (or any part thereof) with or without notice, without liability to you or any third party.</p></div><div class='section'><h3>8. External software</h3><p>You may not use external services, software or networks to automatically create or to augment your creation of stories.</p></div><div class='section'><h3>9. Golbin can terminate your use of the service</h3><p>Oooo, scary. But true. Golbin, in its sole discretion, may terminate your password, account or use of or access to the Service, and remove and discard any Story, for any reason. Some of the more likely reasons for termination are inaccurate information in the registration form, or harassment of other StoryTellers (this is a BIG no no), bloggers and other individuals online. More reasons include hacking Stories or the Service, automatically redirecting story traffic to another site, spamming people on and off the site, illegal transactions via Golbin, and otherwise acting in violation of the terms or the spirit of these Terms of Service or other policies making an StoryTellers a fine, upstanding member of the Golbin community. If Golbin terminates your use of the Service, then your Story may be immediately taken down, and your Golbin Earnings Account may be closed. In this event, Golbin will not be responsible to you or any third party for any termination of your access to the Service.</p></div><div class='section'><h3>10. Golbin proprietary rights</h3><p>You acknowledge and agree that the Service and any necessary software used in connection with the Service (&quot;Software&quot;) contain proprietary and confidential information that is protected by applicable intellectual property and other laws.</p></div><div class='section'><h3>11. Disclaimer of waranties</h3><p>The Service is provided on an &quot;as is&quot; and &quot;as available&quot; basis. We're not perfect, but we're getting better every day! You expressly understand and agree that your use of the Service is at your sole risk. Golbin expressly disclaims all warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including, but not limited to the implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and non-infringement. Golbin makes no warranty that the service will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error-free (gremlins happen!), or that the quality of any products, services, information, or other material purchased or obtained by you through the service will meet your expecta